// K + P + 64 = 0 (mod 512)
// 64 char512
void MD5::Padding(const string& str) {
long length = str.length(), total_length = 0, zero_num;
// char 8 bit 512 bit 64 char
if (length % 64 < 56) {
zero_num = 56 - length%64 - 1; // 1
total_length = (length/64+1) * 64;
} else {
zero_num = 64 - length%64 + 56 - 1; // 1
total_length = (length/64+2) * 64;
}
padding_message = new u_char[total_length];
memcpy(padding_message, str.c_str(), length);
// 1
padding_message[length] = 0b10000000;
for (int i = 1; i <= zero_num; i++) {
padding_message[i+length] = 0;
}
// 64
long bit_length = length * 8;
for (int j = 0; j < 8; j++) {
padding_message[total_length - 1 - j] = ((bit_length << 8*j) >> 56);
}
block_size = total_length / 64;
}

CV[1] = 0xefcdab89;
CV[2] = 0x98badcfe;
CV[3] = 0x10325476;
}

CV
F, G, H, I T T[]

4 64

// 4 ()
u_int F(u_int x, u_int y, u_int z) { return (x & y) | ((~x) & z); }
u_int G(u_int x, u_int y, u_int z) { return (x & z) | (y & (~z)); }
u_int H(u_int x, u_int y, u_int z) { return (x ^ y ^ z); }
u_int I(u_int x, u_int y, u_int z) { return (y ^ (x | ~z)); }
(1) A a <- b + ((a + g(b, c, d) + X[k] + T[i]) <<<s)
(2) (A, B, C, D) (B, C, D, A) <- (A, B, C, D)
a, b, c, d : MD (A, B, C, D)
g : (F, G, H, I )
<<< s: 32 (CLS) s
X[k]: k (k = 0..15) 32
T[i] : T i 32 T 64
+ : 2^32

// MD5 4
void MD5::H_MD5(u_char X[64]) {
u_int a = CV[0], b = CV[1], c = CV[2], d = CV[3];
RoundFunc ArrFunc = { F, G, H, I}; //
for (int i = 0; i < 4; i ++) { //
for (int j = 0; j < 16; j++) {
// a = b + ((a + g(b, c, d) + X[k] + T[i]) <<<s)
int k = X_table[i][j];
u_int t = b + CycleMoveLeft(a + ArrFunc[i](b, c, d) + charToUint(X+k*4)
+ T[16*i+j], s[i][j]);
// (A, B, C, D)
a = d; d = c; c = b; b = t;
}
}
CV[0] += a; CV[1] += b; CV[2] += c; CV[3] += d;
}

void MD5::HexOutput() {
for (int i = 0; i < 4; i++) {
for (int j = 0; j < 4; j++) {
cout << hex << ((CV[i] << (3-j)*8) >> 24); //
}
}
cout << endl;
}
